question.text:
Match the following column I with column II:
  Column-I   Column-II
(A) Homo habilis (I) first human-like being hominid
(B) Homo erectus (II) buried their dead with flowers
(C) Neanderthal man (III) brain size around 900cc
(D) Cro-magnon man (IV) excellent cave painting/art

solution.text: The first human-like being the hominid and was called Homo habilis. Neanderthal man buried their dead with flowers. Homo erectus had a large brain around 900 cc. Cromagnon man were known for excellent cave art/painting.
